  Uninstall --purge-project-state literal,uninstall (typed-literal confirm)

deferredWork[3]:
  Phase 14 cross-boundary refactor opportunity: extract commandReferencesHook + LOOM_HOOKS manifest from register-loom-hooks.ts as a shared module so /loom-uninstall doesn't duplicate LOOM_HOOK_NAMES. Future cleanup wave.
  README references /loom-doctor and /loom-uninstall — lightweight wording sync may be needed if their final flags drift.
  Phase 11A README absorbed the legacy Starting points/Status sections — wave-6 review should sanity-check that brownfield/greenfield routing reads well after the restructure.

keyDecisions[3]:
  test/docker/run-harness.sh --mode curl runs install.sh from a staging dir; --mode plugin extracts tarball under ~/.claude/plugins/loom. Defaults to plugin (preserves Phase 8 S-01 behavior).
  /loom-update marker discipline: write before exec; clear on success; preserve for --resume on failure; terminal "failed" sentinel on unrecoverable resume.
  /loom-uninstall strict-abort: --purge-project-state typed-literal failure aborts the WHOLE run (no mutation). Safe-by-default reading of S-02; flip the early return if partial-mutation is intended later.

